In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 15 to October 15 as National Hispanic Heritage Month in the United States. He highlights the significant contributions of Hispanics to the country, including their commitment to family, faith, hard work, and service. The president emphasizes the importance of ensuring opportunities for all Americans, including Hispanics, by promoting economic growth, improving education, expanding access to healthcare, and addressing immigration reform. He calls upon public officials, educators, and the American people to observe the month with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs under the theme "Renewing the American Dream."